Node.Notes: Uncertain. Masoretic text seems most naturally read as: the ephod went down [to David in Keilah] in his [i.e., Abiathar’s] hand.
Assumes two coordinate pp as P: David [was] in the desert of Ziph, at Horesh (the second being a more specific location than the first).
Uncertain whether 3651 functions as ADV or as a predicate adjective in an implied clause: certainly knows [this] or knows [that this is] true.
